# Core rules (always on)

Stack: monorepo · Node.js + NestJS + REST · Sequelize (`@nestjs/sequelize` +
`sequelize-typescript`) · MySQL · React + TS + Vite. Do not change the stack.
No GraphQL. No alternative ORM/DB/UI-kit.

**Language:** all code, identifiers and comments in English. Keep these domain terms
in Spanish, never translate: OUV, PRE, PRI, SER, Preventa, Pricing, ICP, MOFU, RFS,
RFB, WinRate, ChurnRate, segmentos (Gobierno, D&S, B2B).

**Module boundaries:** 10 modules (auth, audit, demand-generation, qualification,
discovery, technical-feasibility, pricing, offer-closing, implementation, post-sales).
Never import another module's internals; call its public service only. Shared code (if ever needed) → root `shared/`.

**Always:** validate inputs (DTO + class-validator); every create/update/delete is audited;
no secrets in code (use env). Consecutivos OUV/PRE/PRI/SER are immutable once issued and
generated atomically.

**UI:** never hardcode a hex or font. Use `frontend/src/styles` tokens. Palette is Verytel only.
`Aller` font is for the logo SVG only.

When unsure, prefer the smallest change that fits these rules and ask.
